23:43.560 --> 23:44.280
And David Cruz.

23:44.280 --> 23:47.100
One of the present masters of science fiction and fantasy,

23:47.300 --> 23:50.720
an author whose work stretches back four decades into the golden age of science fiction,

23:50.860 --> 23:51.380
is Poole Anderson.

23:51.940 --> 23:53.060
It's hard to type Anderson.

23:53.360 --> 23:57.040
He's a full-time professional who writes all kinds of fantasy and science fiction.

23:57.500 --> 23:59.840
He's known as a writer of hard science, for example,

24:00.220 --> 24:03.720
which can be seen in novels like Tau Zero or The Man Who Counts,

24:03.980 --> 24:05.540
a fine example of world building.

24:06.020 --> 24:07.680
He's constructed two future histories.

24:08.140 --> 24:10.420
The best known one, the history of the Polycystoknecht League,

24:10.420 --> 24:14.780
contains some of his most famous characters and some of his most fascinating alien cultures.

24:15.600 --> 24:18.500
Some of the best of contemporary fantasy comes from his pen also,

24:18.720 --> 24:21.880
in novels like The Broken Sword and Three Hearts and Three Lions.

24:22.320 --> 24:24.380
And he sometimes writes tongue-in-cheek spooks,

24:24.440 --> 24:25.960
as in his novel The High Crusade,

24:26.360 --> 24:30.260
in which the medieval warriors with swords conquer a space-faring galactic civilization.

24:30.840 --> 24:33.900
Anderson has won numerous Nebula and Hugo awards for his fiction,

24:34.120 --> 24:36.860
and he served as president of the Science Fiction Writers of America.

24:37.320 --> 24:39.060
He knows the field like few others do.

24:39.060 --> 24:42.500
We asked him if science fiction has changed in the years he's been writing it.

24:43.120 --> 24:45.800
Oh yes, I've been a great many changes.

24:49.040 --> 24:51.720
Back around 1940 or so,

24:54.120 --> 25:01.440
well, practically all you could get, unless you heart back to a few writers like Wells and Bern,

25:01.840 --> 25:05.500
practically all you could get was in a few pulp magazines.

25:11.660 --> 25:12.860
Nowadays, of course,

25:14.940 --> 25:17.100
there's an overwhelming flood of it.

25:18.660 --> 25:21.600
It is not possible to read all which appears.

25:22.600 --> 25:25.580
Anderson thinks the image of science fiction has changed over the years.

25:26.480 --> 25:34.180
And also, of course, it's no longer disreputable. It's become quite respectable.

25:34.180 --> 25:41.020
Oh, you know, when I was your age, it was unthinkable

25:41.020 --> 25:44.740
that anybody could arrange a telephone interview with

25:45.720 --> 25:51.180
one of the writers of it under the auspices of a college for heaven's sake.

25:52.800 --> 25:57.300
But Lord, this was pulp fiction. It was beyond the pale.

25:59.880 --> 26:05.760
Nowadays, it's been tough in college courses and all, you know, all this other stuff, you know.

26:33.340 --> 26:36.520
He believes that science fiction has had an important impact on the public,

26:36.780 --> 26:38.900
and he tells us why he thinks science fiction is valuable.

26:40.080 --> 26:45.300
Actually, all this is kind of trivial. I think the important thing is that

26:46.080 --> 26:52.260
the basic concepts have sort of permeated the public mind.

26:52.260 --> 27:04.820
And I think people are aware in that nowadays, in a way that they never used to be aware,

27:06.120 --> 27:11.300
that the future is going to be different from the past. It may be better. It may be worse,

27:11.900 --> 27:17.720
whatever, but it's going to be different and in very fundamental ways.

27:20.040 --> 27:24.780
And they tend to accept this, be prepared for it.

27:26.360 --> 27:33.840
I often say that perhaps the most important public service that science fiction is doing

27:35.160 --> 27:40.900
is by casting a certain glamour over science and technology.

27:40.900 --> 27:50.680
It recruits a lot of young people into these fields and heaven knows we need an awful lot of

27:50.680 --> 27:56.940
scientists and technologists. Anderson is still going strong today. You'll find his latest work at any bookstore.

